<div xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" class="tagDoc" id="tagDesc_beam"><h2>&lt;beam&gt; beam</h2><h3>Description:</h3><p> A container for a series of explicitly beamed events that begins and ends entirely
      within a measure. For beams that cross the barline, use the beamspan element. Secondary
      beams may be broken explicitly using the breaksec attribute on the notes or chords under
      the beam. Automated beaming, as opposed to explicitly marked beams, may be indicated for
      an entire score, part or section by using the beam.group and beam.rests attributes on
      these elements. 
   </p><h3>May contain:</h3><p><a title="Show description of add-element" href="/documentation/tagLibrary/add">add</a>,
